Two police officers were arrested on Tuesday for kidnapping of a 60-year-old woman in Kayole, Nairobi. The woman was picked up her residence in Embakasi and taken to a house where she was held hostage by three men. The three, among them a civilian, demanded a ransom from the woman who called her son and informed him of the incident. It remains unclear how much they asked for before they could release the woman. The officers, who work under the Railways police division, were arrested by their colleagues from Kayole police station. They are under interrogation before they are taken to court. Click here for the latest political news